{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Summary\n\nCharacterize — and, only if a gap is confirmed, detect — the **refusal-as-content** failure\nmode in rebar's LLM structured-output path: a provider content-policy refusal returned as a\nnormal-looking TEXT/verdict rather than raising, so an LLM gate (review / verify-completion /\nplan-review) could read a refusal as a valid result.\n\n## Why (background)\n\npydantic-ai **#5221** (+ fix PR **#6167**) reports that a content-policy refusal can come back\nas a plain text part with `response.status='incomplete'` / `incomplete_details.reason=\n'content_filter'` and NO structured refusal object. pydantic-ai's own agent loop only raises\n`ContentFilterError` when the parts are **empty**, so a refusal-as-content (non-empty\n`TextPart`) is returned to the caller as normal output.\n\n**Note on provider:** #5221 is about **OpenAI** (`finish_reason='content_filter'`), not\nAnthropic — this ticket's title conflates them. rebar runs Anthropic (`claude-*`), where the\nanalogous signal is `stop_reason=\"refusal\"` (see `src/rebar/llm/errors.py:40`,\n`src/rebar/llm/structured.py:231`). The failure *shape* (a refusal surfaced as content) is\nprovider-independent; the characterization must confirm which signals Anthropic-via-pydantic-ai\nactually emits for a refusal.\n\n**rebar already has a partial defense** (from closed story 978d,\n`jade`-adjacent silent-success work): `structured.check_stop_reason(stop_reason)`\n(`src/rebar/llm/structured.py:249`) raises `UnretryableOutputError` on\n`{refusal, max_tokens, length, content_filter}`, and the runner calls it on BOTH output paths\n(`runner.py:519` PromptedOutput, `runner.py:539` NativeOutput) reading\n`run_result.response.finish_reason`. So IF pydantic-ai reliably surfaces\n`finish_reason`/`stop_reason` for a refusal-as-content turn, rebar already fails closed. The\nopen question this ticket answers is whether that signal is reliably present, or whether a\nrefusal can slip through with an unset/`stop` finish_reason.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Construct (or capture via a cassette) a pydantic-ai `ModelResponse` representing an\n   Anthropic refusal-as-content turn: a non-empty `TextPart` carrying refusal prose. Vary the\n   `finish_reason`/`stop_reason` across `{\"refusal\", None, \"stop\", \"content_filter\"}`.\n2. Drive it through rebar's structured path (`runner.py` NativeOutput + PromptedOutput →\n   `structured.check_stop_reason`) for a gated op (e.g. `verify_completion`).\n3. Observe whether rebar RAISES (`UnretryableOutputError`) or returns the refusal prose as a\n   (hollow but valid-looking) verdict.\n\n- **Expected:** any refusal-as-content turn fails closed — rebar raises a typed refusal error\n  and never returns the refusal as a usable verdict/review result.\n- **Actual (to be characterized):** unknown. If `finish_reason` is reliably `refusal`/\n  `content_filter`, `check_stop_reason` already catches it (no gap). If a refusal can arrive\n  with `finish_reason` unset/`stop`, the refusal prose is returned as content — the #5221 gap\n  reproduced in rebar.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **Characterized:** a documented determination (a comment/artifact on this ticket, plus a\n  reproduction test) of whether rebar's structured path is vulnerable to refusal-as-content —\n  i.e., whether a refusal turn can be returned as a non-empty valid-looking result that\n  `check_stop_reason` does NOT catch. Cites pydantic-ai #5221 / #6167 and the exact rebar code\n  path (`structured.check_stop_reason`, `runner.py:519/539`).\n- [ ] **If a gap is confirmed:** add a content-level guard (in `src/rebar/llm/structured.py`\n  and/or `runner.py`) that recognizes a refusal-as-content response **independent of\n  finish_reason** and raises the existing `UnretryableOutputError` (fail-closed), so a refusal\n  can never be returned as a valid verdict/review. Covered by a unit test that simulates a\n  refusal-as-content `ModelResponse` with an unset finish_reason and asserts it raises.\n- [ ] **If NO gap** (the finish_reason/stop_reason signal is reliably present for our provider\n  and `check_stop_reason` already fails closed): document why, add a **regression test** that\n  pins that a refusal-as-content turn raises (so a future pydantic-ai/provider change can't\n  silently reopen the gap), and close as characterized-not-vulnerable.\n- [ ] File paths: `src/rebar/llm/structured.py`, `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`,\n  `src/rebar/llm/errors.py`; tests under `tests/unit/`.\n\n## Notes / decisions to confirm on review\n\n- Desired posture is **fail-closed** (a refusal → typed error, never a PASS) per the user's\n  earlier direction. Confirm this over warn-only or retry.\n- Scope is the structured/verdict path (the LLM gates). Non-structured/free-text LLM calls (if\n  any) are out of scope unless the characterization shows they share the defect.","title":"Characterize + detect refusal-as-content in the structured-output path (pydantic-ai #5221)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783745606953904001,"uuid":"991dea35-c7f3-4bb8-a78e-f22bc65ab4ef"}